searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Application","doc":"OTP application entrypoint for the API service.\n\nSupervised children:\n- `VpnApi.Repo` — Ecto repository (PostgreSQL connection pool).\n- `Bandit` — HTTP server running the `VpnApi.Router` on configured `app_port`.\n\nThe listening port is taken from the `:vpn_api, :app_port` application env.","ref":"VpnApi.Application.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Application.start/2","doc":"Starts the supervision tree for the API service.\n\nReturns `{:ok, pid}` or `{:error, reason}` as per `Supervisor.start_link/2`.","ref":"VpnApi.Application.html#start/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Core.Log","doc":"Structured JSON logging helpers built on top of `Logger`.\n\nAll logs include a UTC timestamp, level, event name, and module. Optional\nfields: `:req_id`, `:user_id`, `:details`, `:fingerprint`.","ref":"VpnApi.Core.Log.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Core.Log.error/4","doc":"Logs an error event as a JSON line with `error_code`.","ref":"VpnApi.Core.Log.html#error/4"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Core.Log.info/3","doc":"Logs an info event as a JSON line.","ref":"VpnApi.Core.Log.html#info/3"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Core.Retry","doc":"Simple retry helper with exponential backoff (up to 3 attempts).\n\nBackoff: `250ms * 4^attempt + jitter(0..200ms)`.","ref":"VpnApi.Core.Retry.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Core.Retry.with_backoff/1","doc":"Calls `fun` until it returns `{:ok, value}` or attempts are exhausted.\n\nReturns the `{:ok, value}` on success, otherwise `{:error, :max_retries}`.","ref":"VpnApi.Core.Retry.html#with_backoff/1"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Repo","doc":"Ecto repository for the API service.\n\n- Uses `Ecto.Adapters.Postgres`.\n- Reads its configuration from the `:vpn_api` OTP application environment.","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.aggregate/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.aggregate/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#aggregate/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.aggregate/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.aggregate/4 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#aggregate/4"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.all/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.all/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.all_by/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.all_by/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#all_by/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.checked_out?/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.checked_out?/0 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#checked_out?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.checkout/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.checkout/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#checkout/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.child_spec/1","doc":"","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.config/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.config/0 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#config/0"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.default_options/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.default_options/1 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#default_options/1"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.delete/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.delete!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete!/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#delete!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.delete_all/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete_all/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#delete_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.disconnect_all/2","doc":"Forces all connections in the repo pool to disconnect within the given interval.\n\nOnce this function is called, the pool will disconnect all of its connections\nas they are checked in or as they are pinged. Checked in connections will be\nrandomly disconnected within the given time interval. Pinged connections are\nimmediately disconnected - as they are idle (according to `:idle_interval`).\n\nIf the connection has a backoff configured (which is the case by default),\ndisconnecting means an attempt at a new connection will be done immediately\nafter, without starting a new process for each connection. However, if backoff\nhas been disabled, the connection process will terminate. In such cases,\ndisconnecting all connections may cause the pool supervisor to restart\ndepending on the max_restarts/max_seconds configuration of the pool,\nso you will want to set those carefully.","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#disconnect_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.exists?/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.exists?/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#exists?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.explain/3","doc":"Executes an EXPLAIN statement or similar for the given query according to its kind and the\nadapter in the given repository.","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#explain/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - VpnApi.Repo.explain/3","doc":"# Postgres\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, Post)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\"\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.explain(Repo, :all, Post)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\"\n\n    # MySQL\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, from(p in Post, where: p.title == \"title\")) |> IO.puts()\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n    | id | select_type | table | partitions | type | possible_keys | key  | key_len | ref  | rows | filtered | Extra       |\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n    |  1 | SIMPLE      | p0    | NULL       | ALL  | NULL          | NULL | NULL    | NULL |    1 |    100.0 | Using where |\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n\n    # Shared opts\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, Post, analyze: true, timeout: 20_000)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=443) (actual time=0.013..0.013 rows=0 loops=1)\\nPlanning Time: 0.031 ms\\nExecution Time: 0.021 ms\"\n\nIt's safe to execute it for updates and deletes, no data change will be committed:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(Repo, :update_all, from(p in Post, update: [set: [title: \"new title\"]]))\n    \"Update on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=449)\\n  ->  Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=449)\"\n\nThis function is also available under the repository with name `explain`:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, from(p in Post, where: p.title == \"title\"))\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\\n  Filter: ((title)::text = 'title'::text)\"","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#explain/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - VpnApi.Repo.explain/3","doc":"Built-in adapters support passing `opts` to the EXPLAIN statement according to the following:\n\nAdapter          | Supported opts\n---------------- | --------------\nPostgrex         | `analyze`, `verbose`, `costs`, `settings`, `buffers`, `timing`, `summary`, `format`, `plan`\nMyXQL            | `format`\n\nAll options except `format` are boolean valued and default to `false`.\n\nThe allowed `format` values are `:map`, `:yaml`, and `:text`:\n  * `:map` is the deserialized JSON encoding.\n  * `:yaml` and `:text` return the result as a string.\n\nThe built-in adapters support the following formats:\n  * Postgrex: `:map`, `:yaml` and `:text`\n  * MyXQL: `:map` and `:text`\n\nThe `:plan` option in Postgrex can take the values `:custom` or `:fallback_generic`. When `:custom`\nis specified, the explain plan generated will consider the specific values of the query parameters\nthat are supplied. When using `:fallback_generic`, the specific values of the query parameters will\nbe ignored. `:fallback_generic` does not use PostgreSQL's built-in support for a generic explain\nplan (available as of PostgreSQL 16), but instead uses a special implementation that works for PostgreSQL\nversions 12 and above. Defaults to `:custom`.\n\nAny other value passed to `opts` will be forwarded to the underlying adapter query function, including\nshared Repo options such as `:timeout`. Non built-in adapters may have specific behaviour and you should\nconsult their documentation for more details.\n\nFor version compatibility, please check your database's documentation:\n\n  * _Postgrex_: [PostgreSQL doc](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/sql-explain.html).\n  * _MyXQL_: [MySQL doc](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/explain.html).","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#explain/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.get/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.get!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get!/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#get!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.get_by/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_by/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#get_by/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.get_by!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_by!/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#get_by!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.get_dynamic_repo/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_dynamic_repo/0 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#get_dynamic_repo/0"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.in_transaction?/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.in_transaction?/0 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#in_transaction?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.insert/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#insert/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.insert!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert!/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#insert!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.insert_all/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_all/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#insert_all/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.insert_or_update/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_or_update/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#insert_or_update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.insert_or_update!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_or_update!/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#insert_or_update!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.load/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.load/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#load/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.one/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.one/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#one/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.one!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.one!/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#one!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.preload/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.preload/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#preload/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.prepare_query/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.prepare_query/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#prepare_query/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.prepare_transaction/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.prepare_transaction/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#prepare_transaction/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.put_dynamic_repo/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.put_dynamic_repo/1 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#put_dynamic_repo/1"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.query/3","doc":"Runs a custom SQL query.\n\nIf the query was successful, it will return an `:ok` tuple containing\na map with at least two keys:\n  * `:num_rows` - the number of rows affected\n  * `:rows` - the result set as a list. `nil` may be returned\n    instead of the list if the command does not yield any row\n    as result (but still yields the number of affected rows,\n    like a `delete` command without returning would)","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - VpnApi.Repo.query/3","doc":"* `:log` - When false, does not log the query\n  * `:timeout` - Execute request timeout, accepts: `:infinity` (default: `15000`);","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - VpnApi.Repo.query/3","doc":"iex> MyRepo.query(\"SELECT $1::integer + $2\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, %{rows: [[42]], num_rows: 1}}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.query(MyRepo, \"SELECT $1::integer + $2\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, %{rows: [[42]], num_rows: 1}}","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.query!/3","doc":"Same as `query/3` but returns result directly without `:ok` tuple\nand raises on invalid queries","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"Runs a custom SQL query that returns multiple results on the given repo.\n\nIn case of success, it must return an `:ok` tuple containing a list of\nmaps with at least two keys:\n\n  * `:num_rows` - the number of rows affected\n\n  * `:rows` - the result set as a list. `nil` may be returned\n    instead of the list if the command does not yield any row\n    as result (but still yields the number of affected rows,\n    like a `delete` command without returning would)","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query_many/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - VpnApi.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"* `:log` - When false, does not log the query\n  * `:timeout` - Execute request timeout, accepts: `:infinity` (default: `15000`);","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query_many/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - VpnApi.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"iex> MyRepo.query_many(\"SELECT $1; SELECT $2;\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, [%{rows: [[40]], num_rows: 1}, %{rows: [[2]], num_rows: 1}]}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.query_many(MyRepo, \"SELECT $1; SELECT $2;\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, [%{rows: [[40]], num_rows: 1}, %{rows: [[2]], num_rows: 1}]}","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query_many/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.query_many!/3","doc":"Same as `query_many/4` but returns result directly without `:ok` tuple\nand raises on invalid queries","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#query_many!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.reload/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.reload/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#reload/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.reload!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.reload!/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#reload!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.rollback/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.rollback/1 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#rollback/1"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.start_link/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.start_link/1 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.stop/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.stop/1 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#stop/1"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.stream/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.stream/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#stream/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.to_sql/2","doc":"Converts the given query to SQL according to its kind and the\nadapter in the given repository.","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#to_sql/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - VpnApi.Repo.to_sql/2","doc":"The examples below are meant for reference. Each adapter will\nreturn a different result:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.to_sql(:all, Post)\n    {\"SELECT p.id, p.title, p.inserted_at, p.created_at FROM posts as p\", []}\n\n    iex> MyRepo.to_sql(:update_all, from(p in Post, update: [set: [title: ^\"hello\"]]))\n    {\"UPDATE posts AS p SET title = $1\", [\"hello\"]}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.to_sql(:all, MyRepo, Post)\n    {\"SELECT p.id, p.title, p.inserted_at, p.created_at FROM posts as p\", []}","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#to_sql/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.transact/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.transact/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#transact/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.transaction/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.transaction/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#transaction/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.update/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.update!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update!/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#update!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Repo.update_all/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update_all/3 .","ref":"VpnApi.Repo.html#update_all/3"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Router","doc":"Minimal REST API for managing users, nodes, credentials and issuing VLESS links.\n\nEndpoints (JSON):\n- `GET /health` — health probe.\n- `POST /v1/users` — create user by Telegram id.\n- `POST /v1/issue` — issue VLESS link for a user on a node.\n- `POST /v1/nodes/:id/sync` — render and write Xray config for a node.\n- `POST /v1/nodes/:id/reload` — hot‑reload Xray via docker signal.\n- Nodes CRUD: `GET /v1/nodes`, `POST /v1/nodes`, `GET/patch/delete /v1/nodes/:id`.\n\nResponses are JSON; errors share the shape\n`%{error: true, error_code: String.t(), event: String.t(), details: map()}`.","ref":"VpnApi.Router.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Router.call/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"VpnApi.Router.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Router.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.init/1 .","ref":"VpnApi.Router.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Credential","doc":"Credential linking a user to a node with a VLESS UUID.\n\nUsed for generating per‑user client entries in Xray config and issuing links.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Credential.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Credential.changeset/2","doc":"Validates creation/update params for a credential and enforces constraints.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Credential.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Event","doc":"Append‑only event log entry associated with a user.\n\nCaptures timestamp `ts`, event name, and arbitrary `payload_json`.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Event.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Event.changeset/2","doc":"Validates event attributes. Requires `:ts` and `:event`.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Event.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Node","doc":"Node model representing a VPN server instance.\n\nCaptures network location, REALITY parameters and housekeeping fields used\nto render and synchronize Xray configuration.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Node.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Node.changeset/2","doc":"Validates creation/update params for a node, including listen port bounds.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Node.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Payment","doc":"Payment record for tracking user top‑ups or charges.\n\nFields include `amount` (integer, in minor units), `currency`, `status`,\n`provider`, and an opaque `meta_json` for provider payloads.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Payment.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Payment.changeset/2","doc":"Validates creation/update params for a payment.\nRequires `:user_id`, `:amount (> 0)`, `:currency`.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Payment.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Subscription","doc":"Subscription record describing a user's plan, quota and expiry.\n\nTracks `bytes_limit`/`bytes_used` counters and `expires_at` timestamp.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Subscription.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.Subscription.changeset/2","doc":"Validates creation/update params for a subscription.\nRequires `:user_id`, `:plan`; enforces positive `:bytes_limit`.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.Subscription.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.User","doc":"User model representing a Telegram user.\n\nFields: `tg_id` (integer), `status` (string).\nAssociations: subscriptions, credentials, payments, events.\nEncoded to JSON with selected fields for API responses.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.User.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Schemas.User.changeset/2","doc":"Validates creation/update params for a user.\n\nRequires positive `:tg_id`; limits `:status` length.","ref":"VpnApi.Schemas.User.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Vless","doc":"Helper to construct `vless://` links compatible with REALITY + Vision.\n\nEncodes optional parameters for Reality transport such as `public_key`,\n`short_id`, `server_name`, and a human label appended after `#`.","ref":"VpnApi.Vless.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Vless.render/2","doc":"Build a VLESS link from a credential UUID and options.\n\nOptions:\n- `:host` (default: \"localhost\")\n- `:port` (default: 443)\n- `:public_key` (Reality public key)\n- `:short_id` (Reality short id)\n- `:server_name` (SNI)\n- `:label` (label after '#', URL‑encoded)\n\nReturns `{:ok, binary}` or `{:error, %{error_code: \"VPN-003\", reason: term}}`.","ref":"VpnApi.Vless.html#render/2"},{"type":"module","title":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer","doc":"Builds an Xray REALITY VLESS configuration and manages hot reloads.\n\nResponsibilities:\n- `render/2` — create in‑memory Xray JSON config from params and client UUIDs.\n- `write!/2` — write JSON config to a file (defaults to `/xray/config.json`).\n- `reload/0` — send `USR1` to the `xray` docker container to hot‑reload.\n\nExpected params keys for `render/2` (with defaults):\n- `\"listen_port\"` (443), `\"dest\"` (\"www.cloudflare.com:443\"),\n  `\"serverNames\"`, `\"privateKey\"`, `\"publicKey\"`, `\"shortIds\"`.","ref":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.html"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.reload/0","doc":"Hot‑reload Xray by signaling the `xray` docker container with `USR1`.\n\nRetries with backoff up to 3 times; returns `:ok` on success.","ref":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.html#reload/0"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.render/2","doc":"Render an Xray REALITY VLESS config for given params and client UUIDs.\n\nReturns `{:ok, map}` with the config or `{:error, %{error_code: String.t(), reason: term}}`.","ref":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.html#render/2"},{"type":"function","title":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.write!/2","doc":"Encode the config to JSON and write it to `path`.\n\nReturns `:ok` or `{:error, %{error_code: \"VPN-003\", reason: term}}`.","ref":"VpnApi.Xray.Renderer.html#write!/2"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.38.3"}}